nodes.body:
Here are the [benchmark results](http://speed.lean-fro.org/mathlib4/run-detail/a37bbbb7-b207-45d0-afe5-eee2f0a7a1a2) for commit cb4d250d59b5487a9537879c219dd454138eed95.
There were [significant changes](http://speed.lean-fro.org/mathlib4/compare/8bd5e7c7-b1de-4792-92ff-276e19ef9dd3/to/a37bbbb7-b207-45d0-afe5-eee2f0a7a1a2) against commit 25c534098076855b4605e2633ccb66b069e6a28b:
```diff
  Benchmark                            Metric         Change
  ==========================================================
+ build                                linting         -5.6%
+ ~Mathlib.RingTheory.IntegralDomain   instructions   -39.7%
```
Is that PR the start of the doom of Type-valued default fields?
For now I think it's only the ones involved in diamonds that matter. There'd be no benefit to changing `sub` and `div`.
`pow` and `zpow` are probably also not worth the trouble; but `nat/int/ratCast` are next in line.

Pull request successfully merged into master.

Build succeeded:
  * [Build](https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/actions/runs/8216093200/job/22470260764)
  * [Check all files imported](https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/actions/runs/8216093200/job/22470260660)
  * [Lint style](https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/actions/runs/8216093200/job/22470260711)
Maybe make a separate issue or add to an existing one.
I guess this caused the speedup?

pullRequest.title: [Merged by Bors] - refactor: do not allow `qsmul` to default automatically
